commit.message: Audiosync is finally available for Gentoo end-users :)

Miscellaneous fixes thanks to clang-tidy (#27)

* More const usage
* Closing file descriptors in case of error in ffmpeg_pipe to avoid file
descriptor overflow
* UNUSED() in bindings.c
* audiosync_abort() called always before anything else in case of error
* avoid using memset() for arrays of doubles
Initialize at the top & const improvements
free() after threads finish, fixes tests
Including Python tests on Travis CI
Handling unused variables with the new macro UNUSED(x)
Renamed module from vidify_audiosync to audiosync
